+	See detail in aufs.5.
+config AUFS_DLGT
+	bool "Delegate the internal branch access the kernel thread"
+	depends on AUFS
+	default n
+	help
+	If you want aufs to delegate the internal access to the
+	branches which is made by aufs, to the kernel thread, in order
+	to hide the access issued by your application from your LSM or
+	something or make your application to be traced strictly by
+	the task I/O accounting, then enable this option and use
+	'dlgt' mount option.
+	It will damage the performance.
+	See detail in aufs.5.
+config AUFS_RR_SQUASHFS
+	bool "Make squashfs branch RR (real readonly) by default"
+	depends on AUFS
+	default y
+	help
+	If you use squashfs or LZMA patched squashfs as an aufs branch
